    {
        "content": "<p>Does it help if you do all your processing and printing inside the <code>withImportModules</code>? Also, note the new restriction about env extensions mentioned in <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Lean.withImportModules#doc\">docs#Lean.withImportModules</a>; this may or may not cause problems for you.</p>",
        "id": 524470015,
        "sender_full_name": "Jannis Limperg",
        "timestamp": 1750171386
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This would be equivalent to</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">env</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">importModules</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c\">/-</span><span class=\"cm\"> processing goes here -/</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>right? In this case, I can't do that, because the memory needs to be freed, otherwise my memory runs out if processing, say, more than 5 files.</p>",
        "id": 524471435,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Merten",
        "timestamp": 1750171792
    }
]